<section class="py-20 px-6 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-[#0C447C] mb-4 text-center">Not a git log. A handoff note.</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-center mb-10">This is what <code class="text-sm bg-white px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono border border-slate-200">.lodestar.md</code> looks like — the kind of note a thoughtful colleague would write after watching your session.</p>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
        <div class="flex gap-1.5">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-slate-200"></div>
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-slate-200"></div>
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-slate-200"></div>
        </div>
        <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono ml-2">.lodestar.md</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 overflow-x-auto">
        <div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mb-4"># Lodestar Context</div>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="text-[#185FA5] font-semibold mb-2">## Decisions</div>
          <div class="ml-4 space-y-3">
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Switched from REST to tRPC for the API layer</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Rationale: Type safety end-to-end without code generation. Simpler DX for a solo founder.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Onboarding flow: email-first, not social auth</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Rationale: Target users are developers — they distrust OAuth popups. Email + magic link converts 2x better in our persona.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Ship free tier before Pro — no paywall at launch</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Rationale: Community trust and adoption rate matter more than early revenue. Gate Pro features, not the core tool.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Added Drizzle ORM instead of Prisma</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Rationale: Prisma's cold start time was adding 2-3s to serverless invocations.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="text-[#185FA5] font-semibold mb-2">## Rejected Approaches</div>
          <div class="ml-4 space-y-3">
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Prisma ORM</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Reason: Binary dependency caused 2-3s cold starts on Vercel serverless.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold">Multi-step onboarding wizard</div>
              <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Reason: Tested a 3-step flow — 40% drop-off at step 2. Replaced with single-screen setup.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-[#185FA5] font-semibold mb-2">## Open Questions</div>
          <div class="ml-4 space-y-1">
            <div class="text-xs"><span class="text-red-500 font-bold">[BLOCKING]</span> Drizzle push or migrate workflow for production?</div>
            <div class="text-xs"><span class="text-slate-400">[non-blocking]</span> Should the dashboard show usage analytics to free users?</div>
            <div class="text-xs"><span class="text-slate-400">[non-blocking]</span> Landing page hero: illustration vs terminal screenshot?</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
